<title>JAPAN: Nissan Mutual to write off 5 bln yen in bad loans.</title>
<headline>Nissan Mutual to write off 5 bln yen in bad loans.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-11-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nissan Mutual Life Insurance Co said on Thursday that it plans to write off five billion yen worth of bad loans in the current business year to March 31.</p>
<p>The company said it expects to resolve its bad loan problem by the end of the 1998/99 business year.</p>
<p>The company also said that it plans to reduce its investment in foreign bonds in the second half of the current business year in light of foreign exchange risks.</p>
